body_html: I believe this is related to Python's confusing import semantics, which make problems likely if a local module shadows the name of a standard library one. The easiest fix is probably to rename your local queue.py, or move it into a submodule (I can't tell from the path if your queue module would be imported as queue or Hand.queue in your program; if the former then I think you'll need to move it).

body: I believe this is related to Python's confusing import semantics, which make problems likely if a local module shadows the name of a standard library one. The easiest fix is probably to rename your local `queue.py`, or move it into a submodule (I can't tell from the path if your `queue` module would be imported as `queue` or `Hand.queue` in your program; if the former then I think you'll need to move it).
